d where identities are challenged and defined, reinforcing tradition and commanding innovation.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aLibraries and society. 0aLibrariesxHistory. 4aLibrary Architecture. 4aLibrary History. 4aLibrary Trends. 4aLibrary User. 4aSocial Media. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aKimball, Melanie A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWisser, Katherine M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2017z9783110547863oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831104485660 cprintz978311044833740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045084240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110450842423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110450842.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LB  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017